cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the problem of two-way relaying and proposes a new transmission protocol to recover the spectral loss. Information theory is closely related to the study of communication systems and transmission protocols. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the problem of non-simultaneous data exchange in cellular systems and proposes a new protocol to overcome this issue. This is a networking problem and falls under the scope of cs.NI. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the problem of two-way relaying and proposes a new transmission protocol to improve the spectral efficiency. This is a communication problem and falls under the scope of cs.COMM. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a structured precoder to cancel the back-propagating interference in the proposed transmission protocol. This involves the design of a control system and falls under the scope of cs.SY. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) nodes and proposes a precoder that triangulates the compound MAC and BC phase MIMO channels. This is related to the transmission of multimedia data and falls under the scope of cs.MM.
